pr_review_comment_body:
@vltr  What's your thought on this? Should the default recommendation be to use `@sanic_jwt.protected` or just `@protected`.

`@sanic_jwt.protected` clearly has the benefit of greater flexibility.
`@protected` has the benefit of simplicity since there is no need to pass around that instance. It is much easier to break an app into smaller modules and files and pull the decorator from a package than from an instance.

Since the text_log_error table is currently append only (i.e. we don't change the data in any way), you can use the trick I outlined in my document of:

```sql
create table text_log_error_copy like text_log_error;
... make modifications to text_log_error_copy...
insert into text_log_error_copy select * from text_log_error;
SET @max_id = (select max(id) FROM text_log_error_copy);
insert into text_log_error_copy select * from text_log_error where id>@max_id; 
rename table text_log_error_copy to text_log_error, text_log_error to text_log_error_old;
```

(you may want to add in a lock table to do the last bit, should be easy but I haven't yet researched exactly how this would be done)

