What about a more complex version:

```Python
        new_position = 0
        if whence == os.SEEK_SET:
            new_position = offset
        elif whence == os.SEEK_CUR:
            new_position = self.pos + offset
        elif whence == os.SEEK_END:
            new_position = self.max_size + offset

        if new_position < 0:
            return -1

        if new_position < self.max_size:
            self.pos = new_position
        else:
            logger.warning("Symbolic seek: maximum file length reached")
            self.pos = self.max_size

        return self.pos
```

I'm not sure on how to handle the last case. I guess one can drop the last if/else. Technically there is no problem setting the position behind max_size. A read/write access should warn about it.

