You can simply do:
```Python
if provider:
  return [client.get(...)]
else:
  return client.list(...)
```
In this case both "show" and list return lists. Show doesn't return an individual object like VM show does. It returns a list of things for single provider.  That's the same paradigm as list/list-all.

At least, that's what I gather from the help text.  What does the output look like for "show" vs. "list"?

